    "body": "> @Texnomic need more info. network, command-line, which exact RPC are you using, what is `eth_syncing` and why you mention \"Streaming\" here.\r\n\r\n@mandrigin I mentioned `Streaming` as in RPC Method `eth_subscribe` + `newPendingTransactions` \r\n\r\n#### Network:\r\nMainnet (Synced)\r\n\r\n#### Command:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nrpcdaemon --ws --grpc --pprof --metrics --metrics.expensive --grpc.healthcheck --datadir /mnt/data/ --private.api.addr 127.0.0.1:9090 --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --metrics.addr 0.0.0.0 --metrics.port 6071 --verbosity 4 --http.port 8545 --http.vhosts '*' --http.api eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool,db,parity --pprof.port 6063  \r\n```\r\n\r\n#### RPC:\r\n`eth_subscribe` -> `newPendingTransactions` -> `eth_getTransactionByHash` -> `null`",
